    grammar: { title: `Question tags — Petites questions de confirmation`, content: `Question tags are short questions added at the end of a statement to check or confirm: 'You're coming, aren't you?' (Tu viens, non ?). 'She didn't call, did she?' (Elle n'a pas appelé, si ?). The rule: positive statement → negative tag; negative statement → positive tag. The auxiliary verb matches the main clause: 'It is...' → 'isn't it?', 'They have...' → 'haven't they?', 'You went...' → 'didn't you?', 'He can...' → 'can't he?'. In real conversation, the intonation matters more than the exact form — a falling intonation means you expect agreement, a rising intonation means you're genuinely asking.` },
