    grammar: { title: `Conditional sentences type 2 — Situations hypothétiques`, content: `The second conditional describes imaginary or unlikely situations: 'If + past simple, would + infinitive'. Examples: 'If I had more time, I would learn to paint' (Si j'avais plus de temps, j'apprendrais à peindre). 'If I were you, I'd take the deal' (Si j'étais toi, je prendrais l'accord). Note: we often say 'if I were' not 'if I was', especially in formal English. This is different from the first conditional (real possibility): 'If I have time, I will help you' vs 'If I had time, I would help you'. Second conditional = imaginary or very unlikely.` },
